properties.name: fileUri
properties.description: The path to the video on the device.

properties.name: outputFileName
properties.description: The file name for the transcoded video

properties.name: outputFileType
properties.description: Instructions on how to encode the video. Android is always mp4

properties.name: optimizeForNetworkUse
properties.description: Should the video be processed with quailty or speed in mind. iOS only

properties.name: saveToLibrary
properties.description: Save the new video the library. Not supported in windows. Defaults to true

properties.name: deleteInputFile
properties.description: Delete the original video. Android only. Defaults to false

properties.name: videoBitrate
properties.description: Bitrate in bits. Defaults to 1 megabit (1000000).

properties.name: fps
properties.description: Frames per second of the result. Android only. Defaults to 24.

properties.name: audioChannels
properties.description: Number of audio channels. iOS only. Defaults to 2.

properties.name: audioSampleRate
properties.description: Sample rate for the audio. iOS only. Defaults to 44100

properties.name: audioBitrate
properties.description: Sample rate for the audio. iOS only. Defaults to 128 kilobits (128000).

properties.name: progress
properties.description: Not supported in windows, progress on the transcode. info will be a number from 0 to 100
